00:45:00.670 --> 00:45:01.170
Hi.

00:45:01.170 --> 00:45:03.390
You said you actually
were an expert

00:45:03.390 --> 00:45:05.460
in classical architecture.

00:45:05.460 --> 00:45:07.710
How do you see this as an
evolution of what the Greeks

00:45:07.710 --> 00:45:10.500
and Romans were trying to do?

00:45:10.500 --> 00:45:12.990
Because there's are quite
mathematical as well,

00:45:12.990 --> 00:45:14.070
their architecture.

00:45:14.070 --> 00:45:16.440
Do you think this is just
the evolution of that,

00:45:16.440 --> 00:45:18.610
or is this something
totally different?

00:45:18.610 --> 00:45:20.580
MARIO CARPO: Well,
architecture is always

00:45:20.580 --> 00:45:24.180
at the mercy of the tools
we use to make it happen.

00:45:24.180 --> 00:45:25.680
That's inevitable.

00:45:25.680 --> 00:45:27.570
To some extent,
every expression is

00:45:27.570 --> 00:45:30.350
at the mercy of the tool
we use to manifest it.

00:45:30.350 --> 00:45:32.380
You can think that
language is natural,

00:45:32.380 --> 00:45:36.035
but in fact, when your ideas are
manifested through the alphabet

00:45:36.035 --> 00:45:38.805
or through syntax,
the tools that you

00:45:38.805 --> 00:45:41.640
use to communicate feedback
on the kind of message

00:45:41.640 --> 00:45:43.950
you can, you know, transmit.

00:45:43.950 --> 00:45:47.610
This feedback loop is inevitable
in every human expression.

00:45:47.610 --> 00:45:50.220
In the case of architecture, if
you compare it with painting,

00:45:50.220 --> 00:45:56.080
the technical bottleneck
is more determinant.

00:45:56.080 --> 00:45:58.660
Of course, a painter
is at the mercy

00:45:58.660 --> 00:46:01.810
of the kind of canvas he's
using and the technology

00:46:01.810 --> 00:46:03.970
of the colors he's
putting on the canvas,

00:46:03.970 --> 00:46:07.086
but you can think that
that technological--

00:46:07.086 --> 00:46:11.200
the limitation, it's not
much if you compare it

00:46:11.200 --> 00:46:14.110
with the technical implication
of building a big building.

00:46:14.110 --> 00:46:16.030
And we are particularly
at the mercy

00:46:16.030 --> 00:46:18.040
of tools of
quantification, because we

00:46:18.040 --> 00:46:20.350
have to measure a building
before it is built,

00:46:20.350 --> 00:46:22.206
and that was always
the case in Greek,

00:46:22.206 --> 00:46:23.830
and Roman, and
classical architecture--

00:46:23.830 --> 00:46:25.660
not so much for
costing or estimate,

00:46:25.660 --> 00:46:28.220
which is important today,
but for proportions,

00:46:28.220 --> 00:46:30.730
which, for them, was a
matter of vital importance.

00:46:30.730 --> 00:46:34.990
And evidently, if you look at
Roman or Greek architecture,

00:46:34.990 --> 00:46:38.120
you can glean, from the way
the buildings are built,

00:46:38.120 --> 00:46:40.780
the kind of tools
of quantification

00:46:40.780 --> 00:46:44.140
they used to make it happen,
which was not number based,

00:46:44.140 --> 00:46:46.990
because the Greek and Roman
didn't have good numbers,

00:46:46.990 --> 00:46:48.430
and they didn't trust numbers.

00:46:48.430 --> 00:46:50.350
It was all based on geometry.

00:46:50.350 --> 00:46:54.040
What we would solve
by using, you know,

00:46:54.040 --> 00:46:55.570
Hindu-Arabic numbers--

00:46:55.570 --> 00:46:58.420
which evidently we didn't have--
the numbers they had were crap,

00:46:58.420 --> 00:47:01.030
and so they couldn't use
them to calculate anything.

00:47:01.030 --> 00:47:03.670
But their geometry
was first class.

00:47:03.670 --> 00:47:04.990
We still use it.

00:47:04.990 --> 00:47:09.040
So all that quantification
was achieved through Euclidean

00:47:09.040 --> 00:47:13.520
geometry tools, whereas the
arithmetic number-based tools

00:47:13.520 --> 00:47:16.420
we use today didn't yet exist.

00:47:16.420 --> 00:47:19.430
You know, the Greeks
always mistrusted numbers.

00:47:19.430 --> 00:47:22.790
They preferred geometry
were all in the compass,

00:47:22.790 --> 00:47:25.250
the typical tool of the masons.

00:47:25.250 --> 00:47:30.580
The quantification of
the proportional harmony

00:47:30.580 --> 00:47:33.820
of those buildings derived from
that use of geometry, which

00:47:33.820 --> 00:47:37.090
is why neoclassical architecture
as of a 17th century

00:47:37.090 --> 00:47:39.290
or 18th century-- which
is number-based and not

00:47:39.290 --> 00:47:42.670
geometrical determined-- from
a distance, it looks the same.

00:47:42.670 --> 00:47:45.940
But if you look at it
with the eye of an expert,

00:47:45.940 --> 00:47:48.790
you can tell that
it's no longer Euclid.

00:47:48.790 --> 00:47:50.360
It is numbers.

00:47:50.360 --> 00:47:53.980
Those numbers were
pure arithmetics.

00:47:53.980 --> 00:47:57.640
The story I've told you
is how quantification

00:47:57.640 --> 00:48:00.850
shifted from
algebra to calculus,

00:48:00.850 --> 00:48:04.480
because this is what Bezier
and the French teams did.

00:48:04.480 --> 00:48:06.400
In a sense, that
was the culmination

00:48:06.400 --> 00:48:08.110
of the dreams of
Western mathematics,

00:48:08.110 --> 00:48:12.310
because with Descartes,
Leibniz, and Newton,

00:48:12.310 --> 00:48:15.020
we could not eat conics--

00:48:15.020 --> 00:48:18.130
you know, parabolas, hyperboles,
et cetera, et cetera.

00:48:18.130 --> 00:48:21.850
With Bezier, it was, in
a sense, the culmination

00:48:21.850 --> 00:48:23.980
of the dream of
mathematicians of all time.

00:48:23.980 --> 00:48:26.980
You can notate, using
a mathematical script,

00:48:26.980 --> 00:48:27.850
everything.

00:48:27.850 --> 00:48:31.140
A cloud in the sky, a
flower in the field,

00:48:31.140 --> 00:48:34.210
any shape and form in
nature can be scripted

00:48:34.210 --> 00:48:36.280
as a mathematical notation.

00:48:36.280 --> 00:48:38.770
Of course, we didn't need to
notate the cloud or a flower.

00:48:38.770 --> 00:48:40.690
We need to notate
the body of a car.

00:48:40.690 --> 00:48:43.840
And it was complicated, but
with computers, it became easy.

00:48:43.840 --> 00:48:45.940
Which is why when
computers became available,

00:48:45.940 --> 00:48:48.580
first thing we did-- we didn't
use them to make potatoes.

00:48:48.580 --> 00:48:50.980
We used them to make fish,
because that's mathematics,

00:48:50.980 --> 00:48:52.780
and there is no
mathematics in a potato.

00:48:52.780 --> 00:48:55.150
We call this freeform,
because there is

00:48:55.150 --> 00:48:57.140
no mathematics embedded in it.

00:48:57.140 --> 00:49:00.970
And in a sense, that dog,
the last part of my story,

00:49:00.970 --> 00:49:03.220
is closer to the
potato than the fish.

00:49:03.220 --> 00:49:05.300
So in a sense, we are
getting back to a potato,

00:49:05.300 --> 00:49:08.860
but with a delay of 24 years.

00:49:08.860 --> 00:49:11.550
But the feedback loop
back to your question--

00:49:11.550 --> 00:49:15.190
at every point in time, the
kind of architectural shapes

00:49:15.190 --> 00:49:16.720
and form you see--

00:49:16.720 --> 00:49:18.910
if you look at it as an
historian of science,

00:49:18.910 --> 00:49:22.920
you can read in
the physical shape,

00:49:22.920 --> 00:49:24.790
the tools of
quantification which were

00:49:24.790 --> 00:49:27.580
essential to make it happen.

00:49:27.580 --> 00:49:30.100
That doesn't mean that I can
do that for every period.

00:49:30.100 --> 00:49:34.300
I can only do it for some
little passages in it,

00:49:34.300 --> 00:49:36.058
but that's the game.

